{"title_page": "SEAT Exeo", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox automobile\n| name = SEAT Exeo\n| image = 2011 SEAT Exeo Sport Tech CR TDi 168 2.0 Front.jpg\n| manufacturer = [[SEAT]]\n| production = 2008\u20132013\n| predecessor = [[SEAT 132]]<br />[[SEAT Bolero]] (concept)\n| successor = [[SEAT Le\u00f3n]] (estate)<br />[[SEAT Toledo]] (saloon)\n| assembly = Spain: [[Martorell]]\n| class = [[Large family car]] ([[D-segment|D]])\n| body_style = 4-door [[sedan (automobile)|saloon]]<br />5-door [[station wagon|estate]]\n| layout = [[Front-engine, front-wheel-drive layout|Front-engine, front-wheel-drive]]\n| platform = [[Volkswagen Group B platform#B7|Volkswagen Group B7]]\n| engine = ''[[Petrol engine]]s:''<br />1.6&nbsp;L [[Inline-four engine|I4]]<br />1.8&nbsp;L I4 16v [[Gasoline direct injection|TSI]]<br />1.8&nbsp;L I4 [[Multi-valve|20v]] [[Turbocharger|Turbo]]<br />1.8&nbsp;L I4 16v TSI<br />2.0&nbsp;L I4 16v TSI<br />''[[Diesel engine]]s:''<br />2.0&nbsp;L I4 16v [[Turbocharged Direct Injection|TDI]] [[Common rail|CR]]\n| transmission = 6-speed [[Manual transmission|manual]]<br />6/7-speed LuK [[multitronic]] [[continuously variable transmission|CVT]]\n| wheelbase = {{convert|2642|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n| length = {{convert|4661|mm|1|abbr=on}} (saloon)<br />{{convert|4666|mm|1|abbr=on}} (estate)\n| width = {{convert|1772|mm|1|abbr=on}}\n| height = {{convert|1430|mm|1|abbr=on}} (saloon)<br />{{convert|1454|mm|1|abbr=on}} (estate)\n| weight = {{convert|1310|-|1455|kg|0|abbr=on|lk=on}}\n| related = [[Audi A4#B7|Audi A4 (B7)]]/[[Volkswagen Passat|Volkswagen Passat (B7)]]\n| designer = \n| sp = uk\n}}\n\nThe '''SEAT Exeo''' ({{IPA-es|ek\u02c8se.o|lang}})<ref name=CAR>{{cite web|title=SEAT names its new Exeo flagship|url=http://www.carmagazine.co.uk/News/Search-Results/Industry-News/Seat-Names-Its-New-Exeo-Flagship/|publisher=[[Car Magazine]]|date=23 June 2008|accessdate=26 January 2010}}</ref><ref name=AW>{{cite web|title=Spain: SEAT Exeo to supplement, not replace Toledo|url=http://www.automotiveworld.com/news/oems-and-markets/69066-spain-seat-exeo-to-supplement-not-replace-toledo|publisher=Automotive World|date=20 June 2008|accessdate=26 January 2010}}</ref><ref name=AutoBlog>{{cite web|title=Paris 2008: <s>Previous Gen Audi A4</s> SEAT Exeo|url=http://www.autoblog.com/2008/10/03/paris-2008-strike-previous-gen-audi-a4-strike-seat-exeo/ |agency= [[SEAT|SEAT S.A.]] / Weblogs, Inc.|publisher=[[Autoblog.com|Autoblog]]|date=3 October 2008|accessdate=26 January 2010}}</ref> is a [[large family car]] and [[Flagship car|flagship model]], that was built by the Spanish car manufacturer [[SEAT]], subsidiary of the [[Volkswagen Group]].\n\nPreviously codenamed ''Bolero'', (though not to be confused with SEAT's [[SEAT Bolero|earlier]] [[concept vehicle|concept car]] bearing the same name) and internally designated ''Typ'' 3R,<ref name=\"ETKA\">{{citation |title=ETKA|publisher=[[Volkswagen Group]]|year=2010|edition=[[SEAT]] Update 325|title-link=ETKA}}</ref> the name ''Exeo'' derives from the [[Latin]] word ''exire'', meaning \"to go beyond\",<ref name=CAR/><ref name=AW/> breaking SEAT's recent tradition to name its cars after Spanish cities.<ref name=CAR/>\n\nThis car was made available in four door [[sedan (automobile)|saloon]] or five door [[stationwagon|estate]] styles only. Production of the Exeo ended in May 2013, with the final production number being 81,552. It was replaced by [[SEAT Toledo]] for the [[sedan (automobile)|saloon]], and the [[SEAT Le\u00f3n|SEAT Le\u00f3n ST]] for the [[station wagon|estate]].\n\n==Overview==\n{{Multiple image | align = left | direction = vertical | width =\n| image1 = 2011 SEAT Exeo Sport Tech CR TDi 168 2.0 Rear.jpg\n| caption1 = Sedan\n| image2 = Seat Exeo ST 2.0 TDI Sport Magicoschwarz Heck.JPG\n| caption2 = ST\n| image3 = Seat Exeo ST 2.0 TDI Sport Magicoschwarz Interieur.JPG\n| caption3 = Interior\n}}\n\nThe Exeo is a [[D-segment]] model, which is built on the [[Volkswagen Group B platform#B7|Volkswagen Group B7 (PL46) platform]]. It is essentially a [[badge engineering|rebadged]] [[Audi A4#B7|Audi A4]] B7 generation,<ref name=CAR/><ref name=AW/> with styling changes to the front and rear by way of unique [[hood (automobile)|bonnet]], [[fender (automobile)|front wing]]s, [[trunk (automobile)|boot lid]], [[vehicle door|door]]s and exterior [[wing mirror|door mirror]]s.<ref name=ETKA/><ref>{{cite web|title=SEAT Exeo revealed and it's a rebadged 2008 Audi A4!|url=http://carscoop.blogspot.com/2008/08/2010-seat-exeo-revealed-and-its.html|publisher=Carscoop|date=24 August 2008|accessdate=26 January 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SEAT Exeo grey-scale images - International Registrations Resulting from International Applications Governed Exclusively or Partly by the 1999 Act and/or the 1960 Act|url=http://www.wipo.int/cgi-hag/guest/ifetch5?ENG+HAGUE-ALL.vdb+12-00+41230016-REVERSE+0+0+-1+F+4+16+1+25+SEP-0/HITNUM,B,,+ON%2fseat/|publisher=[[World Intellectual Property Organization|WIPO]]|date=19 December 2007|accessdate=26 January 2010}}</ref><ref name=Autocar>{{cite web|title=SEAT Exeo leaks out|url=http://www.autocar.co.uk/News/NewsArticle/Audi-A4/234581/|publisher=[[Autocar (magazine)|Autocar]]|date=26 August 2008|accessdate=26 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nIt incorporates interior trim from the A4 Cabriolet, and extensively uses A4 [[Audi A4#B6|B6]] and [[Audi A4#B7|B7]] interior equipment and electrical components.<ref name=ETKA/> To this purpose, the entire Audi A4 B7 [[production line|production]] and [[assembly line]]s from [[Ingolstadt]] were dismantled and installed in Volkswagen Group's related SEAT [[list of Volkswagen Group factories|factory]] in [[Martorell]], Spain.<ref name=CAR/>\n\nThe Exeo was officially revealed at the [[2008 Paris Motor Show]],<ref name=AutoBlog/> and at launch, it was confirmed to be available in just one [[car body style]], as a four [[vehicle door|door]], five seater [[sedan (automobile)|saloon]] (''Typ'' 3R5).<ref name=ETKA/> However, from August 2009, it also became available as a five [[vehicle door|door]], five seater [[station wagon|estate]],<ref name=Autocar/> called Exeo ST (''Typ'' 3R9).<ref name=ETKA/> ST is an abbreviation for Sport Tourer.\n\nIt became available for purchase in [[Western Europe]] in March 2009, with a model lineup which initially included three [[petrol engine]]s and two [[diesel engine]]s, with a third lower-powered {{convert|88|kW|PS bhp|0|lk=on}} diesel engine being added from September 2009.\n\nIn May 2010, three new petrol engines entered production, these were the 1.8 TFSI {{convert|88|kW|PS bhp|0}}, the 1.8 TFSI {{convert|118|kW|PS bhp|0}} and the 2.0 TFSI {{convert|155|kW|PS bhp|0}}.<ref name=ETKA/><ref>{{cite web|title=Seat Exeo mit neuen Motoren|url=http://www.auto-motor-und-sport.de/news/seat-exeo-und-exeo-st-mit-neuen-motoren-seat-exeo-mit-neuen-motoren-1846345.html|publisher=[[Auto, Motor und Sport]]|date=3 May 2010|accessdate=|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Todos los detalles de los nuevos SEAT Exeo 1.8 TSI 120 y 160 CV|url=http://es.autoblog.com/2010/05/21/todos-los-detalles-de-los-nuevos-seat-exeo-1-8-tsi-120-y-160-cv/|publisher=Autoblog|date=21 May 2010|accessdate=|language=Spanish}}</ref> It was available with three different [[trim package|trim levels]]: ''Reference'', ''Stylance'' and ''Sport''.<ref name=ETKA/>\n{{Clear}}\n\n==Awards==\n*''Golden Steering Wheel Award'' 2009 in Switzerland, in the upper medium sedan category<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/498-el-seat-exeo-gana-el-volante-de-oro-2009-en-suiza.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719093258/http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/498-el-seat-exeo-gana-el-volante-de-oro-2009-en-suiza.html |archivedate=2011-07-19 |title=The SEAT Exeo wins the Golden Steering Wheel 2009 award in Switzerland |publisher=SEAT media center |date= |accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref>\n*''Company Car 2009'' in Germany, for the SEAT Exeo ST<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/2009/464-el-nuevo-exeo-st-vehiculo-de-empresa-2009-en-alemania.html |title=The new Exeo ST is the \"Company Car 2009\" in Germany |publisher=SEAT media center |date=22 July 2009 |accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref>\n*''Car of the Year 2010'' in Finland, by the Finnish magazine Tuulilasi<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/561-la-gama-seat-premiada-en-europa.html |title=The SEAT range receives distinctions in Europe |publisher=SEAT media center |date=17 February 2010 |accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref>\n*''Novelty of the Year 2009'' in Catalonia<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/412-el-seat-exeo-distinguido-como-novedad-del-ano-en-cataluna.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719093425/http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/412-el-seat-exeo-distinguido-como-novedad-del-ano-en-cataluna.html |archivedate=2011-07-19 |title=The SEAT Exeo, distinguished as \"Novelty of the Year\" in Catalonia |publisher=SEAT media center |date= |accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Powertrain==\nDue to the Exeo being derived from the [[Audi A4#B7|Audi B7 A4]], it shares the same fundamental [[powertrain]] [[automobile layout|layout]]. It has [[front-engine design|engines mounted at the front]], and they are oriented [[longitudinal engine|longitudinally]], i.e.: \"north south\", rather than the \"east west\" [[transverse engine]] layout used in the remainder of the SEAT range.<ref name=ETKA/>  The [[transmission (mechanics)|gearboxes]] are of a [[transaxle]] type (containing the gearbox, along with the front final drive and [[differential (mechanical device)|differential]]), and are also mounted longitudinally at the rear of the engine.<ref name=ETKA/>\n\nFor the 1.8-litre [[multi-valve|20 valve]] [[turbocharger|Turbo]] [[petrol engine]], one side-mounted [[intercooler]] (SMIC) is fitted to the lower front left of the car, below the left headlamp. For the 2.0&nbsp;TSI petrol,<ref name=AutoBlog/> along with the {{convert|105|and|125|kW|PS bhp|0|lk=on}} {{nowrap|2.0-litre [[Turbocharged Direct Injection]]}} [[diesel engine]]s, these use two SMICs, one below the left and right headlamps.<ref name=ETKA/>\n\nAll diesel engine variants are common rail (CR) Turbocharged Direct Injection (TDI) engines and includes an exhaust [[catalytic converter]] along with a [[diesel particulate filter]] (DPF).<ref name=ETKA/>\n\nTransmission options initially included only a six-speed [[manual transmission|manual gearbox]].<ref name=ETKA/> Shortly after launch, the LuK originated [[multitronic]] [[continuously variable transmission]] (CVT),<ref name=covercars>{{cite web|url=http://www.covercars.com/cars/35860 |title=2011 Seat Exeo Multitronic | publisher=CoverCars|date=8 August 2011 |accessdate=17 February 2011}}</ref> with selectable six or seven speeds,<ref>{{cite web|title=The SEAT Exeo features the Multitronic gearbox in the Diesel engine range|url=http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/740-el-seat-exeo-incorpora-el-cambio-multitronic-en-su-gama-diesel-.html?g2_language=en_GB|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716025741/http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/740-el-seat-exeo-incorpora-el-cambio-multitronic-en-su-gama-diesel-.html?g2_language=en_GB|archivedate=2011-07-16|publisher=SEAT media center|date=27 January 2011|accessdate=}}</ref> became available on models equipped with the 2.0&nbsp;TSI petrol and 2.0&nbsp;TDI diesel engines.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/2009/491-el-seat-exeo-completa-su-gama-con-dos-nuevas-versiones.html |title=The SEAT Exeo range grows with two new versions |publisher=SEAT media center |date=21 September 2009 |accessdate=9 March 2011}}</ref> Distribution of the engine [[torque]] to the driven [[wheel|roadwheels]] is only via the [[front-wheel drive|front wheels]], and there is not a [[four-wheel-drive]] offering, which the Audi A4 used as an option in its 'trademark' [[quattro (four wheel drive system)|quattro]].<ref name=ETKA/>\n\n===Engine specifications===\nAll available [[internal combustion engine]]s are [[inline-four engine|inline four cylinder]] [[four-stroke engine|four stroke]] designs and are based on existing units capable to be fitted longitudinally in the Exeo's PL46 platform and have also been used in other [[marque]]s of the [[Volkswagen Group]]. They all comply with the European [[European emission standards|Euro 5]] emissions standard, and offer the following performance statistics (for the saloon version in standard configuration):<ref name=ETKA/><ref>{{cite web|title=The Exeo range gets new motors and trim levels|url=http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/623-la-gama-exeo-incorpora-nuevos-motores-y-equipamientos.html?g2_language=en_GB|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719094453/http://media.seat.com/en/seat-news/623-la-gama-exeo-incorpora-nuevos-motores-y-equipamientos.html?g2_language=en_GB|archivedate=2011-07-19|publisher=SEAT media center|date=24 May 2010|accessdate=}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:92%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Engine<br />designation!!rowspan=2|[[Engine displacement|Displacement]],&nbsp;[[valvetrain]],<br />fuel system!!rowspan=2|[[List of Volkswagen Group engines|ID code]]!!rowspan=2|{{nowrap|Max. motive [[power (physics)|power]]}}<br />at [[revolutions per minute|rpm]]!!rowspan=2|Max. [[torque]]<br />at rpm!!rowspan=2|{{convert|0|-|100|km/h|0|abbr=on}}!!rowspan=2|Top<br />speed!!rowspan=2|[[Carbon dioxide|CO<sub>2</sub>]]<br />(g/100&nbsp;km)!!rowspan=2|Production<br />dates!!colspan=3|[[Trim package|Trim level]] <small>(saloon)</small>\n|-\n!''<small>Reference''!!''<small>Stylance''!!''<small>Sport''\n|-\n!colspan=\"12\" style=\"text-align:center\"|Petrol engines\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''1.6 SRE'''||1595&nbsp;cc, 8v [[SOHC]]<br />[[multi-point fuel injection]]||[[list of Volkswagen Group petrol engines#ALZ|ALZ]]<br /><small>(EA113)</small>||{{convert|75|kW|PS bhp|0|abbr=on|lk=on}}<br />at 5,600 rpm||{{